    climateNote:
      "In the Jewish world of Paul's day, Abraham was the gold standard. To claim Abraham as your father was to claim covenant membership. The Pharisees traced their entire program of Torah observance back to Abraham's example. For Paul to argue that Abraham was justified before the law, before circumcision, before any act of obedience — that was like telling the entire religious establishment that their greatest hero proves their system wrong.",
